India Stocks in U.S. Tumble to Five-Month Low on Jump in Oil, Food Prices

-- B y   Y e   X i e   a n d   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-02-24T16:15:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/india-stocks-in-u-s-tumble-to-five-month-low-on-jump-in-oil-food-prices.html
  India ’s stocks trading in the U.S.
tumbled to the lowest level since September as food-price
increases accelerated and surging oil prices stoked concern
inflation will lead to higher  interest rates .  The Bank of New York Mellon India ADR Index, which tracks
the country’s American depositary receipts, fell for a fourth
day, declining 1.8 percent to 1173.2 as of 11:02 a.m. New York
time, heading for its lowest close since Sept. 8.  Tata Motors
Ltd ., the nation’s biggest truck-maker, sank 4.7 percent, the
most in a month, to $23.52. ICICI  Bank Ltd., India’s second-
biggest lender, tumbled 2.9 percent, the most in two weeks, to
$42.68.  India’s domestic benchmark Sensex index slid 3 percent
today, to 17,632.41 in Mumbai, the biggest drop since Nov. 3,
2009. The index has lost 14 percent this year, making it the
world’s third-worst performing benchmark index  To contact the reporters on this story:
